* Task 6 fixture (dup-name case): APP/CALLER.NSP
* Demonstrates steplib-chain resolution where the same module name (SHARED)
* exists in multiple libraries (APP and COMMON).
* This caller's current library is APP (path prefix match against config).
* When CALLNAT 'SHARED' is resolved:
* - Current library APP → has SHARED.NSN
* - Expected: resolves to APP/SHARED.NSN (current library wins over steplib)
*
* OQ-3, OQ-5: current library from path; steplib chain non-transitive.
* FR-16, FR-5: steplib-chain resolution order matters.

DEFINE DATA
LOCAL
  1 RESULT (A10)
END DEFINE

* Call to SHARED — should resolve to APP/SHARED.NSN (current library first)
CALLNAT 'SHARED'

* Call to COMMONONLY — exists only in COMMON library, not in APP.
* APP declares steplibs=["COMMON"], so resolution follows the chain.
* Expected: resolves to COMMON/COMMONONLY.NSN (steplib fallback).
CALLNAT 'COMMONONLY'

* Call to ORPHAN — exists only in OTHER library.
* OTHER is declared in the library map but is NOT a steplib of APP.
* APP's chain is [APP, COMMON, SYSTEM]; OTHER is not in the chain.
* Expected: Unresolved(ReasonNoTarget) — unreachable from APP.
CALLNAT 'ORPHAN'

MOVE 'OK' TO RESULT

END
